    <item>
      <title>Three laws of visual communication</title>
      <dc:creator>Marc Vandemeulebroecke</dc:creator>
      <dc:creator>Mark Baillie</dc:creator>
      <dc:creator>Alison Margolskee</dc:creator>
      <dc:creator>Baldur Magnusson</dc:creator>
      <link>https://graphicsprinciples.github.io/posts/201-three-laws-vizcom</link>
      <description>... for the quantitative scientist. Effective visual communication follows three laws: 1.)	Have a clear purpose; 2.)	Show the data clearly; and 3.)	Make the message obvious. These three laws correspond to the three main ingredients of any quantitative work: purpose, data, and message. Getting these right leads to success; failing in any of them leads to overall failure.</description>
